# Android camera quality

**Do not regress capture quality on flagship Android.** Reference device: Samsung Galaxy S26 Ultra.

Before changing camera or upload code, read [docs/CAMERA.md](../../docs/CAMERA.md).

## Hard constraints

- Current capture: **1080p60, 12 Mbps H.264**, CameraX via `flip-camerawesome`
- **No 4K path today** — `Quality.FHD` caps recording; this is the main gap vs native camera
- Upload re-compresses via `react-native-compressor` (`maxSize: 1920`, `auto`) in `caption.tsx` — second quality hit
- Keep `FLIP_ANDROID_CAPTURE` (JS) and `FlipCameraSession` constants (Kotlin) in sync when tuning bitrate/resolution

## When adding features

- Prefer capability detection + fallback over fixed 1080p if extending to 4K
- Surface **actual** capture profile to UI/logs, not assumed values
- Avoid extra re-encode steps in the ATProto upload path unless required by size limits
